  "text": "These results suggest that the two structurally similar compounds may undergo different interactions with the lipid molecules, although both compounds inactivated multiple pathogens [CITATION_1] . In fact, 2,5-dihydroxybenzaldehyde has one more OH group on its benzene ring and has a distribution coefficient (Log D) of 1.10 at neutral pH (7.4), whereas one phenolic group is replaced by a methoxyl group (CH 3 ) in 2-hydroxy-5-methoxybenzaldehyde, which increases its Log D (pH 7.4) to 1.50, rendering it more lipophilic. It seems that the hydrophilic and ionic properties associated with the two phenolic OH groups and the lipophilic properties associated with the benzene moiety facilitate interactions with the monolayer.",
